00:43:22.090 --> 00:43:25.280
&gt;&gt; Hi. Good afternoon.

00:43:25.280 --> 00:43:26.580
Thank you for--

00:43:26.580 --> 00:43:27.880
&gt;&gt; Dava Sobel: Hi.

00:43:27.880 --> 00:43:29.180
&gt;&gt; Your talk.

00:43:29.180 --> 00:43:30.480
A friend of mine from
college is an astronomer.

00:43:30.480 --> 00:43:34.300
She works at Adler
Planetarium in Chicago.

00:43:34.300 --> 00:43:37.470
And I've always admired
her brain and her success.

00:43:37.470 --> 00:43:40.290
And I think she's great.

00:43:40.290 --> 00:43:44.390
And, you know, we're at the
age now, we're in our late 50s.

00:43:44.390 --> 00:43:48.140
Could you tell us like how like
the change for women in science

00:43:48.140 --> 00:43:51.380
and astronomy, from the women
that you profiled in this book,

00:43:51.380 --> 00:43:55.250
to now till, you know,
girls in grade school,

00:43:55.250 --> 00:43:59.020
high school who might be interested
in going to the field of astronomy?

00:43:59.020 --> 00:44:01.140
&gt;&gt; Dava Sobel: I'm not sure
I understand the question.

00:44:01.140 --> 00:44:02.440
Can I tell you--

00:44:02.440 --> 00:44:03.740
&gt;&gt; Well, what has changed?

00:44:03.740 --> 00:44:05.040
And if someone--

00:44:05.040 --> 00:44:06.340
&gt;&gt; Dava Sobel: What has changed?

00:44:06.340 --> 00:44:07.640
&gt;&gt; Yeah.

00:44:07.640 --> 00:44:08.940
&gt;&gt; Dava Sobel: Well, I think there
have been changes back and forth.

00:44:08.940 --> 00:44:13.420
I mean a situation like
this in the 1880s of having

00:44:13.420 --> 00:44:17.190
that many women working together
was highly unusual at the time.

00:44:17.190 --> 00:44:22.200
And yet the work that they did
was acknowledged and accepted.

00:44:22.200 --> 00:44:26.720
And the situation at
Harvard continued up till

00:44:26.720 --> 00:44:29.230
about the start of
the Second World War.

00:44:29.230 --> 00:44:33.320
After that there were
machine computers,

00:44:33.320 --> 00:44:38.430
and less of an emphasis
on hiring women.

00:44:38.430 --> 00:44:43.230
I mean Pickering was a
man of great fairness.

00:44:43.230 --> 00:44:45.230
But he was also very practical.

00:44:45.230 --> 00:44:49.470
A room full of women cost a lot
less than a room full of men.

00:44:49.470 --> 00:44:51.100
It's still true.

00:44:51.100 --> 00:44:58.160 position:56%
So all I can say is may it continue.

00:44:58.160 --> 00:44:59.460
&gt;&gt; Thank you.

00:44:59.460 --> 00:45:01.470 position:56%
&gt;&gt; Dava Sobel: I think the one more,

00:45:01.470 --> 00:45:02.910
do we have time for
one last question?

00:45:02.910 --> 00:45:04.210
Yeah. Great.

00:45:04.210 --> 00:45:05.510
Perfect.

00:45:05.510 --> 00:45:06.810
&gt;&gt; Do you know what the glass
plates were treated with in order

